:math:`\boldsymbol{a} \times \boldsymbol{b}` means the cross product of vectors
:math:`\boldsymbol{a}` and :math:`\boldsymbol{b}`.
The cross product components in the :math:`xyz` reference frame are:

.. math::

  \boldsymbol{a} \times \boldsymbol{b}
  =
  \begin{pmatrix}
  a^yb^z - a^zb^y \\
  a^zb^x - a^xb^z \\
  a^xb^y - a^yb^x \\
  \end{pmatrix}
